This below program demonstrates several commonly used String and Wrapper Class methods in Java. 
It converts a String into a character array using toCharArray(), accesses individual characters using both charAt() and array indexing, and compares Strings using the equals() method. The program also shows how to convert a numeric String into a primitive double using Double.parseDouble(). These operations are frequently used in Java for string manipulation, 
character processing, data validation, and converting text-based input into numeric values for calculation



class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
  String s="hello world";
  
  System.out.println(s.toCharArray());
 
  System.out.println(s.charAt(0));
  char [] arr=s.toCharArray();
  System.out.println(arr[0]);
  System.out.println(s.equals("hello"));
  String d="3.66777";
  System.out.println(Double.parseDouble(d));
    }
}

